ts in `MintableToken._assertMaxSupply()` and blocks payout."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Undistributed emissions still consume the farm's lifetime reward budget","locations":["0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:62","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:95","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:115","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:140","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:151","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:219"],"claim":"`timeData.totalRewardsSupply` is increased immediately by the full notified amount, but rewards are only minted later as users accrue and claim them. If no one is staked, `rewardPerToken()` returns the old value and `updateReward` advances `lastUpdateTime`, permanently skipping elapsed emissions while leaving the full amount booked against the lifetime cap. `finishFarming()` likewise truncates the period early without refunding undistributed rewards from `totalRewardsSupply`.","impact":"The contract can burn large portions of its lifetime reward budget without ever minting them to users. Campaigns may underpay relative to their announced allocation, and after enough empty or aborted periods `notifyRewardAmount()` starts reverting even though a meaningful share of the reserved rewards was never actually distributed.","paths":["Call `notifyRewardAmount()` while `_totalSupply == 0`.","Let part or all of the reward period elapse before anyone stakes.","The first later `stake`, `withdraw`, or `getReward` path runs `updateReward`, which moves `lastUpdateTime` forward while `rewardPerToken()` stays unchanged because supply was zero.","Those skipped emissions are now unreachable, but the full notified amount still counts toward `totalRewardsSupply`.","Similarly, call `finishFarming()` before the period ends; the undistributed remainder is no longer earnable, yet it still remains booked against the farm's lifetime reward limit."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Stake accounting becomes insolvent with fee-on-transfer or rebasing staking tokens","locations":["0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:242","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:249","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:262","0xb3fb1d01b01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:265"],"claim":"`_stake()` credits users with the requested `amount` before checking how many staking tokens the contract actually received, and `_withdraw()` always attempts to return the full nominal amount. With deflationary, fee-on-transfer, or negatively rebasing staking tokens, the internal `_totalSupply`/`_balances` ledger diverges from the contract's real token balance.","impact":"Users can be over-credited relative to assets actually held by the pool, earn rewards on inflated balances, and later withdraw more than they contributed if enough tokens remain. The deficit is absorbed by other depositors, or withdrawals begin reverting once the contract no longer holds enough staking tokens.","paths":["Use a staking token that burns, taxes, or rebases balances downward.","Stake `amount`; the contract records the full amount in `_balances` and `_totalSupply`, but receives less in reality.","Accrue rewards against the inflated recorded balance.","Withdraw the nominal amount; the shortfall is effectively paid from other users' deposits or causes pool-wide withdrawal failures once liquidity runs out."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"96-bit reward supply accounting can wrap and overbook rewards","locations":["0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:20","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:90","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:115","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/staking/StakingRewards.sol:118","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/interfaces/MintableToken.sol:11","0xb3fb1d01b07a706736ca175f827e4f56021b85de/contracts/interfaces/MintableToken.sol:46"],"claim":"`StakingRewards` stores cumulative scheduled rewards in `Times.totalRewardsSupply` as `uint96`, but compares it against a `uint256 maxEverTotalRewards`. In Solidity 0.7.5, `uint96(totalRewardsSupply)` silently truncates if the scheduled amount exceeds `2^96 - 1`, so a reward token configured with a larger cap can make the farm's local accounting wrap to a smaller number and accept more emissions than its real mint budget supports.","impact":"If the reward token's cap exceeds the 96-bit range, the farm can over-schedule rewards and appear healthy until actual minting catches up. Claims then start reverting once the token's true global cap is reached, leaving accrued rewards unpaid.","paths":["Deploy the reward token with `maxAllowedTotalSupply > 2^96 - 1`.","Schedule rewards until cumulative `totalRewardsSupply + _reward` crosses the 96-bit boundary.","`notifyRewardAmount()` stores the wrapped `uint96` value in `timeData.totalRewardsSupply`.","Subsequent notifications compare against the wrapped local value and can succeed even though the true cumulative obligation is already above the token's actual mintable cap.","Later `getReward()` calls revert in `_assertMaxSupply()` when the real cap is finally hit."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex"]}],"rejected_candidates":[]}
